Problem: Power of Four
Topic: Math
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
If n is less than or equal to 0, return false. Otherwise, repeatedly divide n by 4 while it is divisible by 4. If the final value becomes 1, then n is a power of four; otherwise, it is not.

Time Complexity: O(log₄ n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPowerOfFour(int n) {
        if(n<=0){
            return false;
        }
        while(n%4==0){
            n/=4;
        }
        return n==1;
    }
};
